  "texts": [
    "The downstream SoftMax function, discussed in the next subsection, normalizes the scores to produce a normalized distribution of weights used to produce the weighted sum of value vectors.",
    "Intuition: The query representation vector of a token embedding corresponds to a \"question\" about how relevant other tokens are in relation to that token.",
    "The key representation vector of a token embedding corresponds to an \"answer\" to the query that quantifies the relevance of each key to the query.",
    "Each value representation vector of a token embedding contains the information that the corresponding token in the X matrix represents.",
    "Figure 6 explains how the matrix multiplication is equivalent to generating an n × n square matrix S of co-relevance scores or dot products."
  ],
